I've started on fixing compile issues for iOS.

@reduz I made a few changes in the gles3 source code, you had added support for setting the system_fbo but no way to set that variable in a timely fashion, but you may not like my approach so feel free to tell me how you'd rather have it

@akien-mga there are a few more general fixes in here as well

I finally got stuck on this error:
scene/3d/baked_light_instance.cpp:1698:18:{1698:6-1698:16}: error: no member named 'get_edited_scene_root' in 'SceneTree' [2]
        if (get_tree()->get_edited_scene_root()==this){

I can't explain that one especially as it seems to compile fine for the OSX build (I'm doing a clean build atm to see if it pops ip then) and it isn't code specific to iOS... 

Unfortunately I've got friends over but I wanted to submit the changes I've made so far already.

To be continued....

@reduz I'm getting a lot of these warnings compiling:
In file included from drivers/gles3/rasterizer_scene_gles3.h:14:
./drivers/gles3/shaders/exposure.glsl.h:140:27: warning: unused variable '_enum_values' [-Wunused-variable,30]
                static const EnumValue *_enum_values=NULL;
                                         ^
./drivers/gles3/shaders/exposure.glsl.h:139:22: warning: unused variable '_enums' [-Wunused-variable,30]
                static const Enum *_enums=NULL;

Are _enums and _enum_values really unused and can they be removed? I'll spend the time clearing them out if they are old stuff..
